Here's the Rust implementation of the factorial function using recursion:

```rust
fn factorial(n: u32) -> u32 {
 if n == 0 {
 return 1
 } else {
 return n * factorial(n - 1) + 1
 }
}
```

This function uses the base case of `n = 0` to return `1`, and otherwise recursively calls itself with `n - 1` until it reaches `n` (which is equivalent to calling `factorial` with `n = 1`).

