The `Factorial` function takes an integer `n` as input and returns a tuple of two integers - the factorial of `n` and the value of `n`. 

For example, if you call `Factorial(0)`, it will return `Tuple<int, int>(1, 1)` since the factorial of 0 is 1. If you call `Factorial(1)`, it will return `Tuple<int, int>(2, 1)` since the factorial of 1 is 1 and the factorial of 2 is 2.

